32:33.940 --> 32:41.560
kind of shift in emphasis in the field of science fiction? No, I don't think it
was a shift in emphasis. I think it was simply that prior to that that there

32:41.560 --> 32:44.880
were stylized

32:44.880 --> 32:52.420
rules of what could be written and what couldn't be written in science fiction,
which were caused by a variety of things, but one, by the fact that science

32:52.420 --> 33:01.180
fiction was perceived by librarians as juvenile literature, so that meant you
had certain limitations in sex. There was an unconscious assumption that you had

33:01.180 --> 33:13.680
to be positive about science. There was a whole set of stylizations and formulas
around the field, And for two generations, the science fiction writers had come

33:13.680 --> 33:22.120
into the field through fandom and through reading other science fiction. In the
60s, a lot of people came into the field from various different directions that

33:22.120 --> 33:29.940
weren't the same as the one unified direction. So people started writing science
fiction to a lot of people, who had very little in common with each other,

33:30.000 --> 33:41.400
except that they were not wedded to the old traditional way of doing things. and
of course this mirrored the cultural climate at the time it mirrored what was

33:41.400 --> 33:49.020
happening politically it mirrored what was happening in music it mirrored what
was happening in movies it was a phenomenon that went through the western

33:49.020 --> 33:58.580
civilization as a whole so in a sense it was a reflection of that in a sense it
was one of the things that caused that because it happened fairly early in

33:58.580 --> 34:07.100
another way it was something that was really catalyzed by Mike Moorcock who was
a very pivotal figure in the whole thing without Mike Boorcock, none of it might

34:07.100 --> 34:19.440
have happened. So it's a mistake to say that this was a school of writing or a
style of writing or any one thing. It wasn't. It was a breaking of the old

34:19.440 --> 34:27.840
conventional parameters. So the people who felt their toes were being stepped on
because these parameters were being broken tried to identify all the various

34:27.840 --> 34:36.940
entirely different things that were breaking the old parameters as one thing, as
the new wave that they could then attack. I mean, it's ridiculous. Anybody that

34:36.940 --> 34:46.760
could have attacked Michael Moorcock as a nihilist was insane because Mike was
the idealist of the age kind of, and he was pumping his own money into this

34:46.760 --> 34:53.800
thing and really had strong idealistic beliefs and they could have been
